      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm currently putting together some personalized training programs for a new group of clients at my gym. To make sure I'm being as efficient as possible with their programming, I wanted to ask from a sports science perspective—are there actually any documented biological differences in things like muscle fiber types, bone density, or general athletic potential between different racial groups that I should be accounting for in my programming?",
